## 4. The Hand Feel Experience

- Impact Sensation
    - Hardness Words: Soft, plush, mushy on hard impact. (~39-41 degrees ESN scale).
    - Feedback: Highly sensory. You feel the ball compressing all the way to the blade.
    - Hold vs. Release: Massive hold (dwell) followed by a springy release.
    - Dwell Time: Extremely long. The ball feels like it rests in the rubber for a fraction of a second.

- Sound/Click
    - Deafeningly loud. This is one of the loudest ESN rubbers on the market, producing a sharp glue-feel click on almost every topspin shot.

