## 5. Compatibility & Setup Guide

- Best Blade Matches
    - Outer Carbon: Excellent pairing. A stiff, crisp outer carbon blade (like Viscaria or Timo Boll ALC) supports the soft sponge, preventing it from feeling too mushy.
    - Inner Carbon: Good pairing for spin-oriented players seeking maximum dwell time and safety.
    - All-Wood: Risky. Pairing a very soft, bouncy rubber with a flexible 5-ply wood blade often results in a muddy, excessively vibrating setup that lacks finishing power.
    - Mismatch Cases: Soft, defensive, or highly flexible 5-ply all-wood blades.

- Forehand vs. Backhand Recommendation
    - Forehand: Only recommended for beginners or players who struggle to generate their own power and need extreme safety.
    - Backhand: Highly recommended. The backhand side typically uses shorter, punchier strokes, making perfect use of FX-P's catapult and easy lifting capabilities.

